<h4>Introduce support for `latest` API</h4>

It is now possible to omit the version number by specifying `Accept: application/vnd.go.cd+json`. This will render the latest version of the API endpoint being invoked. More information can be found [here](https://github.com/gocd/gocd/issues/6620).

<h4> New Pipeline Creation Wizard </h4>

We have rewritten the new pipeline creation flow, to improve the user experience.

Please feel free to report a bug or suggest feedback\ideas by opening up an issue [here](https://github.com/gocd/gocd/issues).

<h4>Java 8 deprecation</h4>

Support for Java 8 will be removed in the next release of GoCD. GoCD (depending on the OS and installer) comes bundled with the supported Java Runtime, hence installing the latest GoCD versions on agent and server should suffice unless you are using a custom Java version.
The removal of Java 8 support is in line with the Java Licensing Changes we had announced earlier this year in this [blog](https://www.gocd.org/2019/05/21/official-stance-on-java/).

<h4>Versions of Java this release of GoCD works with</h4>
<ul>
  <li>Java 8 (Deprecated)</li>
  <li>Java 10 (Deprecated)</li>
  <li>Java 11</li>
  <li>Java 12</li>
</ul>

